wfFrSwDlcmiUnknownRPTErrors.name: wfFrSwDlcmiUnknownRPTErrors

wfFrSwDlcmiCrossNetPollingInterval.description: The number of seconds between successive status enquiry messages.

wfFrSwDlcmiCrossNetAsyncUpdateEnable.description: Indicates whether we are to send to the other end of the network, status updates for dlcis as soon as there is a change of status for the dlci.

wfFrSwDlcmiBcMeasurementEnable.name: wfFrSwDlcmiBcMeasurementEnable
wfFrSwDlcmiBcMeasurementEnable.description: Indicates whether Committed Burst Measurement is enabled for this interface. If this attribute is set to DISABLE then DE bit setting in Frame Relay frames at this interface is disabled.

wfFrSwDlcmiAsyncUpdateEnable.name: wfFrSwDlcmiAsyncUpdateEnable
wfFrSwDlcmiAsyncUpdateEnable.description: Indicates whether the link management entity should send an asynchronous single PVC update message when the state of a PVC is changed by a technician or by cross-net polling procedures.

wfFrSwDlcmiCrossNetListenEnable.name: wfFrSwDlcmiCrossNetListenEnable
wfFrSwDlcmiCrossNetListenEnable.description: Indicates whether the link management entity should make a judgement of the PVC's status based on Cross Net updates.

wfFrSwDlcmiSvcDisable.name: wfFrSwDlcmiSvcDisable
wfFrSwDlcmiSvcDisable.description: Indicates whether SVC is enabled or disabled for this access channel.

wfFrSwDlcmiL2AddrType.name: wfFrSwDlcmiL2AddrType

wfFrSwDlcmiEscapeMode.name: wfFrSwDlcmiEscapeMode
wfFrSwDlcmiEscapeMode.description: Identifies the Escape mode (none, ingress or egress) to be used for PVCs with wfFrSwVcEscapeMode set to enabled.

wfFrSwTupleDlciB.name: wfFrSwTupleDlciB
wfFrSwTupleDlciB.description: Instance identifier; Indicates the DLCI associated with endpoint 'B' of a virtual circuit.

wfFrSwMcastEntry.name: wfFrSwMcastEntry
wfFrSwMcastEntry.description: The parameters for a particular Multicast address.

wfFrSwMcastDelete.name: wfFrSwMcastDelete
wfFrSwMcastDelete.description: Indication to delete this multicast instance.

wfFrSwMcastIndex.name: wfFrSwMcastIndex
wfFrSwMcastIndex.description: Index of this multicast DLCI instance

wfFrSwMcastIpAddr.name: wfFrSwMcastIpAddr
wfFrSwMcastIpAddr.description: IP address of the interface in which this multicast DLCI is defined.

wfFrSwMcastDlci.name: wfFrSwMcastDlci
wfFrSwMcastDlci.description: Identifies the multicast DLCI with which the IndividualDlci is associated.

wfFrSwMcastIndividualDlci.name: wfFrSwMcastIndividualDlci
wfFrSwMcastIndividualDlci.description: Indicates the DLCI associated with the above multicast DLCI.

wfFrSwUsageVolume.name: wfFrSwUsageVolume
wfFrSwUsageVolume.description: Indicates the file system volume number to which the billing usage data files will be written. The volume number corresponds to the slot number on which the volume resides. Note: Value 0 has the special meaning that no 'Store' and 'Flush' operations will take place. This translates to no Billing data will be written to the local file system. 'Update' operations will still be performed on each local slot. Full Billing statistics will still be available in the wfFrSwUsageTable MIB.

wfFrSwUsageVolumeBackup.name: wfFrSwUsageVolumeBackup
wfFrSwUsageVolumeBackup.description: Indicates the backup volume if wfFrSwUsageVolume becomes inoperative. Note: This feature is not implemented in this release.

wfFrSwUsageDirectory.name: wfFrSwUsageDirectory
wfFrSwUsageDirectory.description: The name of the directory where the billing usage data files are stored.

wfFrSwUsageFilePrefix.name: wfFrSwUsageFilePrefix
wfFrSwUsageFilePrefix.description: The base name of billing usage data files.

wfFrSwUsageTimerInterval.name: wfFrSwUsageTimerInterval
wfFrSwUsageTimerInterval.description: This number determines the timer interval (number of seconds) unit for the Billing process to perform its various timer driven tasks. i.e. updating billing usage data, writing billing usage data to file system and file system management activities.

wfFrSwUsageUpdateInterval.name: wfFrSwUsageUpdateInterval
wfFrSwUsageUpdateInterval.description: This number specifies the interval (number of minutes) for the Billing process to collect and update billing usage data in the wfFrSwUsage MIB. Note: When converted to seconds, this must be a multiple of wfFrSwUsageTimerInterval.

wfFrSwUsageStoreInterval.name: wfFrSwUsageStoreInterval
wfFrSwUsageStoreInterval.description: This number specifies the interval (number of minutes) for the Billing process to write billing usage data on to the file system from the wfFrSwUsage MIB. Note: When converted to seconds, this must be a multiple of wfFrSwUsageTimerInterval.

wfFrSwUsageFlushInterval.name: wfFrSwUsageFlushInterval
wfFrSwUsageFlushInterval.description: This number specifies the interval (number of minutes) for the Billing process to write billing usage data on to the file system from the wfFrSwUsage MIB follow by zeroing the wfFrSwUsage MIB. Note: When converted to seconds, this must be a multiple of wfFrSwUsageTimerInterval.

wfFrSwUsageCleanupInterval.name: wfFrSwUsageCleanupInterval
wfFrSwUsageCleanupInterval.description: This is the interval (number of minutes) for the Billing process to check and delete old billing usage data files. Note: When converted to seconds, this must be a multilple of wfFrSwUsageTimerInterval.

wfFrSwUsageLocalTimeZone.name: wfFrSwUsageLocalTimeZone
wfFrSwUsageLocalTimeZone.description: Indicates local time zone of the switch

wfFrSwUsageUpdateTimeStamp.name: wfFrSwUsageUpdateTimeStamp
wfFrSwUsageUpdateTimeStamp.description: Time stamp of last wfFrSwUsageUpdateInterval timer expiration or the starting time of the current wfFrSwUsageUpdateInterval. This value is number of seconds since midnight Jan 1, 1976 (GMT).

wfFrSwUsageStoreTimeStamp.name: wfFrSwUsageStoreTimeStamp
wfFrSwUsageStoreTimeStamp.description: Time stamp of last wfFrSwUsageStoreInterval timer expiration or the starting time of the current wfFrSwUsageStoreInterval. This value is number of seconds since midnight Jan. 1, 1976 (GMT).

wfFrSwUsageFlushTimeStamp.name: wfFrSwUsageFlushTimeStamp
wfFrSwUsageFlushTimeStamp.description: Time stamp of last wfFrSwUsageFlushInterval timer expiration or the starting time of the current wfFrSwUsageFlushInterval. This value is number of seconds since midnight Jan. 1, 1976 (GMT).

wfFrSwUsageCleanupTimeStamp.name: wfFrSwUsageCleanupTimeStamp
wfFrSwUsageCleanupTimeStamp.description: Time stamp of last wfFrSwUsageCleanupInterval timer expiration or the starting time of the current wfFrSwUsageCleanupInterval. This value is number of seconds since midnight Jan. 1, 1976 (GMT).

wfFrSwUsageUpdateData.name: wfFrSwUsageUpdateData
wfFrSwUsageUpdateData.description: Setting this attribute to a non-zero value will cause an immediate updating of the billing usage data. Once activated, this attribute should be reset to zero to allow subsequent activations.

wfFrSwUsageStoreData.name: wfFrSwUsageStoreData
wfFrSwUsageStoreData.description: Setting this attribute to a non-zero value will cause an immediate updating and writing of the billing usage data. Once activated, this attribute should be reset to zero to allow subsequent activations.

wfFrSwUsageFlushData.name: wfFrSwUsageFlushData
wfFrSwUsageFlushData.description: Setting this attribute to a non-zero value will cause an immediate updating and writing of the billing usage data and followed by zeroing the wfFrSwBillingUsage MIB. Once activated, this attribute should be reset to zero to allow subsequent activations.

wfFrSwUsageFileCleanup.name: wfFrSwUsageFileCleanup
wfFrSwUsageFileCleanup.description: Setting this attribute to a non-zero value will cause an immediate checking and deleting old billing usage data files. Once activated, this attribute should be reset to zero to allow subsequent activations.

wfFrSwUsageCurVolume.name: wfFrSwUsageCurVolume
wfFrSwUsageCurVolume.description: current file system volume number used. This number is the same as wfFrSwUsageVolume except when the user sets wfFrSwUsageVolume to an invalid number.

wfFrSwUsageCurVolumeBackup.name: wfFrSwUsageCurVolumeBackup
wfFrSwUsageCurVolumeBackup.description: curent backup file system volume number used. This number is the same as wfFrSwUsageVolumeBackUp except when the user sets wfFrSwUsageVolume to an invalid number. Note: This feature is not implemented in this release.

wfFrSwUsageCurDirectory.name: wfFrSwUsageCurDirectory
wfFrSwUsageCurDirectory.description: current directory name used. This number is the same as wfFrSwUsageDirectory except when the user sets wfFrSwUsageDirectory to an invalid name.

wfFrSwUsageCurFilePrefix.name: wfFrSwUsageCurFilePrefix
wfFrSwUsageCurFilePrefix.description: current base file name used. This number is the same as wfFrSwUsageFilePrefix except when the user sets wfFrSwUsageFilePrefix to an invalid name.

wfFrSwUsageCurTimerInterval.name: wfFrSwUsageCurTimerInterval
wfFrSwUsageCurTimerInterval.description: current timer interval number used. This number is the same as wfFrSwUsageTimerInterval except when the user sets wfFrSwUsageTimerInterval to an invalid value.

wfFrSwUsageCurUpdateInterval.name: wfFrSwUsageCurUpdateInterval
wfFrSwUsageCurUpdateInterval.description: current update interval number used. This number is the same as wfFrSwUsageUpdateInterval except when the user sets wfFrSwUsageUpdateInterval to an invalid value.

wfFrSwUsageCurStoreInterval.name: wfFrSwUsageCurStoreInterval
wfFrSwUsageCurStoreInterval.description: current store timer interval number used. This number is the same as wfFrSwUsageStoreInterval except when the user sets wfFrSwUsageStoreInterval to an invalid value.

wfFrSwUsageCurFlushInterval.name: wfFrSwUsageCurFlushInterval
wfFrSwUsageCurFlushInterval.description: current flush timer interval number used. This number is the same as wfFrSwUsageFlushInterval except when the user sets wfFrSwUsageFlushInterval to an invalid value.

wfFrSwUsageCurCleanupInterval.name: wfFrSwUsageCurCleanupInterval
wfFrSwUsageCurCleanupInterval.description: current file cleanup timer interval number used. This number is the same as wfFrSwUsageCleanupInterval except when the user sets wfFrSwUsageCleanupInterval to an invalid value.

wfFrSwUsageDebug.name: wfFrSwUsageDebug
wfFrSwUsageDebug.description: Enable/Disable printing of debug edl (trap) messages. NOTE: Do not enable this attribute in operational enviornment as it will likely flood the logging facility. This attribute is reserved for specialized debugging in a controlled lab enviornment.

wfFrSwUsageCurDebug.name: wfFrSwUsageCurDebug
wfFrSwUsageCurDebug.description: current debug value used. This value is the same as wfFrSwUsageDebug except when the user sets wfFrSwUsageDeubg to an invalid value.

wfFrSwUsageSwitchId.name: wfFrSwUsageSwitchId
wfFrSwUsageSwitchId.description: switch id used in the billing usage data file.

wfFrSwSvcUsageInterimRecordEnable.name: wfFrSwSvcUsageInterimRecordEnable
wfFrSwSvcUsageInterimRecordEnable.description: Enable/Disable Writing FRSW SVC billing record while SVC connection is still up.

wfFrSwSvcUsageVolume.name: wfFrSwSvcUsageVolume
wfFrSwSvcUsageVolume.description: Indicates the file system volume number to which the SVC billing usage data files will be written. The volume number corresponds to the slot number on which the volume resides. Note: Value 0 has the special meaning that no 'Store' and 'Flush' operations will take place. wfFrSwSvcUsageDirectory.name: wfFrSwSvcUsageDirectory
wfFrSwSvcUsageDirectory.description: The name of the directory where the SVC billing usage data files are stored.

wfFrSwSvcUsageFilePrefix.name: wfFrSwSvcUsageFilePrefix
wfFrSwSvcUsageFilePrefix.description: The base name of SVC billing usage data files.

wfFrSwSvcUsageUpdateInterval.name: wfFrSwSvcUsageUpdateInterval
wfFrSwSvcUsageUpdateInterval.description: This number specifies the interval (number of minutes) for the SVC Billing process to collect and update billing usage data in the wfFrSwUsage MIB. Note: When converted to seconds, this must be a multiple of wfFrSwUsageTimerInterval.

wfFrSwSvcUsageStoreInterval.name: wfFrSwSvcUsageStoreInterval
wfFrSwSvcUsageStoreInterval.description: This number specifies the interval (number of minutes) for the SVC Billing process to write billing usage data on to the file system from the wfFrSwUsage MIB. Note: When converted to seconds, this must be a multiple of wfFrSwUsageTimerInterval.

Note: When converted to seconds, this must be a multiple of wfFrSwUsageTimerInterval.

wfFrSwSvcUsageCleanupInterval.name: wfFrSwSvcUsageCleanupInterval
wfFrSwSvcUsageCleanupInterval.description: This is the interval (number of minutes) for the SVC Billing process to check and delete old billing usage data files. Note: When converted to seconds, this must be a multilple of wfFrSwUsageTimerInterval.

wfFrSwSvcUsageUpdateTimeStamp.name: wfFrSwSvcUsageUpdateTimeStamp
wfFrSwSvcUsageUpdateTimeStamp.description: Time stamp of last wfFrSwSvcUsageUpdateInterval timer expiration or the starting time of the current wfFrSwSvcUsageUpdateInterval. This value is number of seconds since midnight Jan 1, 1976 (GMT).

wfFrSwSvcUsageStoreTimeStamp.name: wfFrSwSvcUsageStoreTimeStamp
wfFrSwSvcUsageStoreTimeStamp.description: Time stamp of last wfFrSwSvcUsageStoreInterval timer expiration or the starting time of the current wfFrSwSvcUsageStoreInterval. This value is number of seconds since midnight Jan. 1, 1976 (GMT).

wfFrSwSvcUsageFlushTimeStamp.name: wfFrSwSvcUsageFlushTimeStamp
wfFrSwSvcUsageFlushTimeStamp.description: Time stamp of last wfFrSwSvcUsageFlushInterval timer expiration or the starting time of the current wfFrSwSvcUsageFlushInterval. This value is number of seconds since midnight Jan. 1, 1976 (GMT).

wfFrSwSvcUsageCleanupTimeStamp.name: wfFrSwSvcUsageCleanupTimeStamp
wfFrSwSvcUsageCleanupTimeStamp.description: Time stamp of last wfFrSwSvcUsageCleanupInterval timer expiration or the starting time of the current wfFrSwSvcUsageCleanupInterval. This value is number of seconds since midnight Jan. 1, 1976 (GMT).

wfFrSwSvcUsageUpdateData.name: wfFrSwSvcUsageUpdateData
wfFrSwSvcUsageUpdateData.description: Setting this attribute to a non-zero value will cause an immediate updating of the SVC billing usage data. Once activated, this attribute should be reset to zero to allow subsequent activations.

wfFrSwSvcUsageStoreData.name: wfFrSwSvcUsageStoreData
wfFrSwSvcUsageStoreData.description: Setting this attribute to a non-zero value will cause an immediate updating and writing of the SVC billing usage data. Once activated, this attribute should be reset to zero to allow subsequent activations.

wfFrSwSvcUsageFlushData.name: wfFrSwSvcUsageFlushData
wfFrSwSvcUsageFlushData.description: Setting this attribute to a non-zero value will cause an immediate updating and writing of the SVC billing usage data and followed by zeroing the wfFrSwBillingUsage MIB. Once activated, this attribute should be reset to zero to allow subsequent activations.

wfFrSwSvcUsageFileCleanup.name: wfFrSwSvcUsageFileCleanup
wfFrSwSvcUsageFileCleanup.description: Setting this attribute to a non-zero value will cause an immediate checking and deleting old SVC billing usage data files. Once activated, this attribute should be reset to zero to allow subsequent activations.

wfFrSwSvcUsageCurVolume.name: wfFrSwSvcUsageCurVolume
wfFrSwSvcUsageCurVolume.description: current file system volume number used for SVC Billing. This number is the same as wfFrSwSvcUsageVolume except when the user sets wfFrSwSvcUsageVolume to an invalid number.

wfFrSwSvcUsageCurDirectory.name: wfFrSwSvcUsageCurDirectory
wfFrSwSvcUsageCurDirectory.description: current directory name used for SVC Billing. This number is the same as wfFrSwSvcUsageDirectory except when the user sets wfFrSwSvcUsageDirectory to an invalid name.

wfFrSwSvcUsageCurFilePrefix.name: wfFrSwSvcUsageCurFilePrefix
wfFrSwSvcUsageCurFilePrefix.description: current base file name used for SVC Billing. This name is the same as wfFrSwSvcUsageFilePrefix except when the user sets wfFrSwSvcUsageFilePrefix to an invalid name.

wfFrSwSvcUsageCurUpdateInterval.name: wfFrSwSvcUsageCurUpdateInterval
wfFrSwSvcUsageCurUpdateInterval.description: current update interval number used. This number is the same as wfFrSwSvcUsageUpdateInterval except when the user sets wfFrSwSvcUsageUpdateInterval to an invalid value.

wfFrSwSvcUsageCurStoreInterval.name: wfFrSwSvcUsageCurStoreInterval

wfFrSwSvcUsageCurFlushInterval.name: wfFrSwSvcUsageCurFlushInterval

wfFrSwSvcUsageCurCleanupInterval.name: wfFrSwSvcUsageCurCleanupInterval

wfFrSwSvcUsageVersionId.name: wfFrSwSvcUsageVersionId
wfFrSwSvcUsageVersionId.description: The Software Version ID field is a two byte, right justified, binary formated value that identifies the particular version number of the software release. High nibble of byte 1 represents the major version number. Low nibble of byte 1 represents the release number. Byte 2 represents the integration number.

wfFrSwUsageSwitchName.name: wfFrSwUsageSwitchName
wfFrSwUsageSwitchName.description: The Switch name is a 6-bytes, right justified with leading blanks as necessary. It can be combination of letters, numbers and blanks. This ID identifies the particular networks equipment for SVC billing usage data process.

wfFrSwUsageDelete.name: wfFrSwUsageDelete
wfFrSwUsageDelete.description: Indicates status of this entry. FRSW_USAGE_CREATED is the normal case. FRSW_USAGE_DELETED means the corresponding tuple and vc instances were deleted some time during this collection interval. This billing instance will be deleted at the end of the next wfFrSwUsageFlush period after this billing record is written out to the file system.

wfFrSwUsageCircuitNumber.name: wfFrSwUsageCircuitNumber
wfFrSwUsageCircuitNumber.description: Instance identifier; the circuit number of this interface.

wfFrSwUsageDlci.name: wfFrSwUsageDlci
wfFrSwUsageDlci.description: Instance identifier; this indicates which virtual circuit.

wfFrSwUsageIPAddress.name: wfFrSwUsageIPAddress
wfFrSwUsageIPAddress.description: (Local) IP address corresponding to wfFrSwUsageCircuitNumber of this virtual circuit.

wfFrSwUsageStartTimeStampHigh.name: wfFrSwUsageStartTimeStampHigh
wfFrSwUsageStartTimeStampHigh.description: Time stamp of the starting time (the high 32 bits) of last billing usage interval. This value is the number of 1/100th seconds since midnight Jan 1, 1976 (GMT).

wfFrSwUsageStartTimeStampLow.name: wfFrSwUsageStartTimeStampLow
wfFrSwUsageStartTimeStampLow.description: Time stamp of the starting time (the low 32 bits) of last billing usage interval. This value is the number of 1/100th seconds since midnight Jan 1, 1976 (GMT).

wfFrSwUsageEndTimeStampHigh.name: wfFrSwUsageEndTimeStampHigh
wfFrSwUsageEndTimeStampHigh.description: Time stamp of the ending time (the high 32 bits) of last billing usage interval. This value is the number of 1/100th seconds since midnight Jan 1, 1976 (GMT).

wfFrSwUsageEndTimeStampLow.name: wfFrSwUsageEndTimeStampLow
wfFrSwUsageEndTimeStampLow.description: Time stamp of the ending time (the low 32 bits) of last billing usage interval. This value is the number of 1/100th seconds since midnight Jan 1, 1976 (GMT).

wfFrSwUsageSentNonDEFramesHigh.name: wfFrSwUsageSentNonDEFramesHigh
wfFrSwUsageSentNonDEFramesHigh.description: Number (the high 32 bits) of local frames sent from this virtual circuit between wfFrSwUsageStartTimeStamp and wfFrSwUsageEndTimeStamp.

wfFrSwUsageSentNonDEFramesLow.name: wfFrSwUsageSentNonDEFramesLow
wfFrSwUsageSentNonDEFramesLow.description: Number (the low 32 bits) of local frames sent from this virtual circuit between wfFrSwUsageStartTimeStamp and wfFrSwUsageEndTimeStamp.

wfFrSwUsageSentNonDEOctetsHigh.name: wfFrSwUsageSentNonDEOctetsHigh
wfFrSwUsageSentNonDEOctetsHigh.description: Number (the high 32 bits) of local octets sent from this virtual circuit between wfFrSwUsageStartTimeStamp and wfFrSwUsageEndTimeStamp.

wfFrSwUsageSentNonDEOctetsLow.name: wfFrSwUsageSentNonDEOctetsLow
wfFrSwUsageSentNonDEOctetsLow.description: Number (the low 32 bits) of local octets sent from this virtual circuit between wfFrSwUsageStartTimeStamp and wfFrSwUsageEndTimeStamp.

wfFrSwUsageSentDEFramesHigh.name: wfFrSwUsageSentDEFramesHigh
wfFrSwUsageSentDEFramesHigh.description: Number (the high 32 bits) of local frames with DE bit sent from this virtual circuit between wfFrSwUsageStartTimeStamp and wfFrSwUsageEndTimeStamp.

wfFrSwUsageSentDEFramesLow.name: wfFrSwUsageSentDEFramesLow
wfFrSwUsageSentDEFramesLow.description: Number (the low 32 bits) of local frames with DE bit sent from this virtual circuit between wfFrSwUsageStartTimeStamp and wfFrSwUsageEndTimeStamp.

wfFrSwUsageSentDEOctetsHigh.name: wfFrSwUsageSentDEOctetsHigh
wfFrSwUsageSentDEOctetsHigh.description: Number (the high 32 bits) of local octets with DE bit sent from this virtual circuit between wfFrSwUsageStartTimeStamp and wfFrSwUsageEndTimeStamp.

wfFrSwUsageSentDEOctetsLow.name: wfFrSwUsageSentDEOctetsLow
wfFrSwUsageSentDEOctetsLow.description: Number (the low 32 bits) of local octets with DE bit sent from this virtual circuit between wfFrSwUsageStartTimeStamp and wfFrSwUsageEndTimeStamp.

wfFrSwUsageLastNonDEFramesHigh.name: wfFrSwUsageLastNonDEFramesHigh
wfFrSwUsageLastNonDEFramesHigh.description: The (high 32 bits) value of wfFrSwCctLocalSentNonDEFrames value at wfFrSwUsageEndTimeStamp. Note: Since wfFrSwCctLocalSentNonDEFrames is a 32-bit COUNTER, this is really a counter keeping track of number of times wfFrSwCctLocalSentNonDEFrames has wrapped around.

wfFrSwUsageLastNonDEFramesLow.name: wfFrSwUsageLastNonDEFramesLow
wfFrSwUsageLastNonDEFramesLow.description: The (low 32 bits) value of wfFrSwCctLocalSentNonDEFrames value at wfFrSwUsageEndTimeStamp.

wfFrSwUsageLastNonDEOctetsHigh.name: wfFrSwUsageLastNonDEOctetsHigh
wfFrSwUsageLastNonDEOctetsHigh.description: The (high 32 bits) value of wfFrSwCctLocalSentNonDEOctets value at wfFrSwUsageEndTimeStamp. Note: Since wfFrSwCctLocalSentNonDEOctets is a 32-bit COUNTER, this is really a counter keeping track of number of times wfFrSwCctLocalSentNonDEOctets has wrapped around.

wfFrSwUsageLastNonDEOctetsLow.name: wfFrSwUsageLastNonDEOctetsLow
wfFrSwUsageLastNonDEOctetsLow.description: The (low 32 bits) value of wfFrSwCctLocalSentNonDEOctets value at wfFrSwUsageEndTimeStamp.

wfFrSwUsageLastDEFramesHigh.name: wfFrSwUsageLastDEFramesHigh
wfFrSwUsageLastDEFramesHigh.description: The (high 32 bits) value of wfFrSwCctLocalSentDEFrames value at wfFrSwUsageEndTimeStamp. Note: Since wfFrSwCctLocalSentNonDEFrames is a 32-bit COUNTER, this is really a counter keeping track of number of times wfFrSwCctLocalSentDEFrames has wrapped around.

wfFrSwUsageLastDEFramesLow.name: wfFrSwUsageLastDEFramesLow
wfFrSwUsageLastDEFramesLow.description: The (low 32 bits) value of wfFrSwCctLocalSentDEFrames value at wfFrSwUsageEndTimeStamp.

wfFrSwUsageLastDEOctetsHigh.name: wfFrSwUsageLastDEOctetsHigh
wfFrSwUsageLastDEOctetsHigh.description: The (high 32 bits) value of wfFrSwCctLocalSentDEOctets value at wfFrSwUsageEndTimeStamp. Note: Since wfFrSwCctLocalSentDEOctets is a 32-bit COUNTER, this is really a counter keeping track of number of times wfFrSwCctLocalSentDEOctets has wrapped around.

wfFrSwUsageLastDEOctetsLow.name: wfFrSwUsageLastDEOctetsLow
wfFrSwUsageLastDEOctetsLow.description: The (low 32 bits) value of wfFrSwCctLocalSentDEOctets value at wfFrSwUsageEndTimeStamp.

wfFrSwUsageRemoteIPAddress.name: wfFrSwUsageRemoteIPAddress
wfFrSwUsageRemoteIPAddress.description: IP address of the other side (remote) of this PVC endpoint.

wfFrSwUsageRemoteDlci.name: wfFrSwUsageRemoteDlci
wfFrSwUsageRemoteDlci.description: DLCI number of the other side (remote) of this PVC endpoint.

wfFrSwVcTable.name: wfFrSwVcTable
wfFrSwVcTable.description: Frame Relay Virtual Circuit table gives information about a virtual circuit.

wfFrSwVcEntry.name: wfFrSwVcEntry
wfFrSwVcEntry.description: An entry in the Frame Relay (Virtual) Circuit table.

wfFrSwVcDelete.name: wfFrSwVcDelete
wfFrSwVcDelete.description: Indication to delete this virtual circuit.

wfFrSwVcCircuit.name: wfFrSwVcCircuit
wfFrSwVcCircuit.description: Instance identifier; the circuit number of this interface (logical port).

wfFrSwVcDlci.name: wfFrSwVcDlci
wfFrSwVcDlci.description: Instance identifier; this indicates the virtual circuit identifier

wfFrSwVcState.name: wfFrSwVcState
wfFrSwVcState.description: Indicates whether the particular virtual circuit is operational.

wfFrSwVcStateSet.name: wfFrSwVcStateSet
wfFrSwVcStateSet.description: User access for setting the state of a virtual circuit

wfFrSwVcMulticast.name: wfFrSwVcMulticast
wfFrSwVcMulticast.description: Indicates whether this dlci is used for multicast or a single destination.

wfFrSwVcInBe.name: wfFrSwVcInBe
wfFrSwVcInBe.description: Indicates the maximum number Incoming Excess Burst bits that are allowed in a configured time interval (T).

wfFrSwVcOutBe.name: wfFrSwVcOutBe
wfFrSwVcOutBe.description: Indicates the Outgoing Excess Burst bits for this virtual circuit.

wfFrSwVcInThroughput.name: wfFrSwVcInThroughput
wfFrSwVcInThroughput.description: Indicates the incoming throughput in bits/sec for this virtual circuit.

wfFrSwVcOutThroughput.name: wfFrSwVcOutThroughput
wfFrSwVcOutThroughput.description: Indicates the outgoing throughput in bits/sec for this virtual circuit.

wfFrSwVcOutBc.name: wfFrSwVcOutBc
wfFrSwVcOutBc.description: Indicates the Outgoing Committed Burst bits for this virtual circuit.

wfFrSwVcInBc.name: wfFrSwVcInBc
wfFrSwVcInBc.description: Indicates the Incoming Committed Burst bits for this virtual circuit.

wfFrSwVcInBcOctets.name: wfFrSwVcInBcOctets
wfFrSwVcInBcOctets.description: Indicates the Incoming Committed Burst in octets for this virtual circuit.

wfFrSwVcReceivedStatus.name: wfFrSwVcReceivedStatus
wfFrSwVcReceivedStatus.description: State of a virtual circuit as reported by the network at an NNI

wfFrSwVcCrossNetStatus.name: wfFrSwVcCrossNetStatus
wfFrSwVcCrossNetStatus.description: State of a virtual circuit as reported by the other end of the network under bidirectional signalling.

wfFrSwVcXNetSent.name: wfFrSwVcXNetSent
wfFrSwVcXNetSent.description: Whether we have sent a cross net status message for this VC yet.

wfFrSwVcXNetReceived.name: wfFrSwVcXNetReceived
wfFrSwVcXNetReceived.description: Whether we have received a cross net status message for this VC during the current polling interval.

wfFrSwVcCalledIpAddr.name: wfFrSwVcCalledIpAddr
wfFrSwVcCalledIpAddr.description: Indicates the IP address associated with destination of a virtual circuit.

wfFrSwVcCalledDlci.name: wfFrSwVcCalledDlci
wfFrSwVcCalledDlci.description: Indicates the DLCI associated with destination of a virtual circuit.

wfFrSwVcTrfPriority.name: wfFrSwVcTrfPriority
wfFrSwVcTrfPriority.description: Defines the traffic priority level of all the incoming packets on this VC. FRSW_VCPRIORITY_DEFAULT - Set all incoming user traffic packets to the default priority used by the port. FRSW_VCPRIORITY_ONE - Set all incoming packets to priority 1. FRSW_VCPRIORITY_TWO - Set all incoming packets to priority 2. FRSW_VCPRIORITY_THREE - Set all incoming packets to priority 3. Priority 0 is reserved for network critical packets like OSPF, FR LMI and SMDS heartbeat and is not available for user traffic.

wfFrSwVcCreationTime.name: wfFrSwVcCreationTime
wfFrSwVcCreationTime.description: Indicates the value of sysUpTime when the VC was created.

wfFrSwVcLastTimeChange.name: wfFrSwVcLastTimeChange
wfFrSwVcLastTimeChange.description: Indicates the value of sysUpTime when last there was a change in VC state.

wfFrSwVcTxNonDeFrames.name: wfFrSwVcTxNonDeFrames
wfFrSwVcTxNonDeFrames.description: Indicates the number of frames without the DE bit sent on this virtual circuit over the interface.

wfFrSwVcTxNonDeOctets.name: wfFrSwVcTxNonDeOctets
wfFrSwVcTxNonDeOctets.description: Indicates the number of octets without DE bit sent on this virtual circuit over the interface.

wfFrSwVcTxDeFrames.name: wfFrSwVcTxDeFrames
wfFrSwVcTxDeFrames.description: Indicates the number of frames with DE bit set sent on this virtual circuit over the interface.

wfFrSwVcTxDeOctets.name: wfFrSwVcTxDeOctets
wfFrSwVcTxDeOctets.description: Indicates the number of octets with DE bit set sent on this virtual circuit over the interface.

wfFrSwVcSetFecnFrames.name: wfFrSwVcSetFecnFrames
wfFrSwVcSetFecnFrames.description: Indicates the number of frames sent to the interface on which this switch set the FECN bit.

wfFrSwVcSetFecnOctets.name: wfFrSwVcSetFecnOctets
wfFrSwVcSetFecnOctets.description: Indicates the number of octets in frames sent to the interface on which this switch set the FECN bit.

wfFrSwVcSetBecnFrames.name: wfFrSwVcSetBecnFrames
wfFrSwVcSetBecnFrames.description: Indicates the number of frames sent to the interface on which this switch set the BECN bit.

wfFrSwVcSetBecnOctets.name: wfFrSwVcSetBecnOctets
wfFrSwVcSetBecnOctets.description: Indicates the number of octets in frames sent to the interface on which this switch set the BECN bit.

wfFrSwVcSetDeFrames.name: wfFrSwVcSetDeFrames
wfFrSwVcSetDeFrames.description: Indicates the number of frames sent to the interface on which this switch set the DE bit.

wfFrSwVcSetDeOctets.name: wfFrSwVcSetDeOctets
wfFrSwVcSetDeOctets.description: Indicates the number of octets in frames sent to the interface on which this switch set the DE bit.

wfFrSwVcDropNonDeFrames.name: wfFrSwVcDropNonDeFrames
wfFrSwVcDropNonDeFrames.description: Indicates the number of frames received over the interface which were discarded, excluding any frames with the DE bit set.

wfFrSwVcDropNonDeOctets.name: wfFrSwVcDropNonDeOctets
wfFrSwVcDropNonDeOctets.description: Indicates the number of octets in frames received over the interface which were discarded, excluding any frames with the DE bit set.

wfFrSwVcDropDeFrames.name: wfFrSwVcDropDeFrames
wfFrSwVcDropDeFrames.description: Indicates the number of frames received over the interface, having the DE bit set, which were discarded.

wfFrSwVcDropDeOctets.name: wfFrSwVcDropDeOctets
wfFrSwVcDropDeOctets.description: Indicates the number of octets in frames received over the interface, having the DE bit set, which were discarded.

wfFrSwVcInactiveVcDropFrames.name: wfFrSwVcInactiveVcDropFrames
wfFrSwVcInactiveVcDropFrames.description: Indicates how many frames were discarded because the virtual circuit was inactive.

wfFrSwVcInactiveVcDropOctets.name: wfFrSwVcInactiveVcDropOctets
wfFrSwVcInactiveVcDropOctets.description: Indicates how many Octets were discarded because the virtual circuit was inactive.

wfFrSwVcRecvNonDeFrames.name: wfFrSwVcRecvNonDeFrames
wfFrSwVcRecvNonDeFrames.description: Indicates the number of frames received on this virtual circuit over the interface.

wfFrSwVcRecvNonDeOctets.name: wfFrSwVcRecvNonDeOctets
wfFrSwVcRecvNonDeOctets.description: Indicates the number of octets received on this virtual circuit over the interface.

wfFrSwVcRecvDeFrames.name: wfFrSwVcRecvDeFrames
wfFrSwVcRecvDeFrames.description: Indicates the number of frames received over the interface with the DE bit set.

wfFrSwVcRecvDeOctets.name: wfFrSwVcRecvDeOctets
wfFrSwVcRecvDeOctets.description: Indicates the number of octets in frames received over the interface with the DE bit set.

wfFrSwVcRecvFecnFrames.name: wfFrSwVcRecvFecnFrames
wfFrSwVcRecvFecnFrames.description: Indicates the number of frames received over the interface with the FECN bit set.

wfFrSwVcRecvFecnOctets.name: wfFrSwVcRecvFecnOctets
wfFrSwVcRecvFecnOctets.description: Indicates the number of octets in frames received over the interface with the FECN bit set.

wfFrSwVcRecvBecnFrames.name: wfFrSwVcRecvBecnFrames
wfFrSwVcRecvBecnFrames.description: Indicates the number of frames received over the interface with the BECN bit set.

wfFrSwVcRecvBecnOctets.name: wfFrSwVcRecvBecnOctets
wfFrSwVcRecvBecnOctets.description: Indicates the number of octets in frames received over the interface with the BECN bit set.

wfFrSwVcRecentNonDeOctets.name: wfFrSwVcRecentNonDeOctets
wfFrSwVcRecentNonDeOctets.description: Indicates the number of octets received over the interface during the most recent sampling period.

wfFrSwVcXNetErrors.name: wfFrSwVcXNetErrors
wfFrSwVcXNetErrors.description: This is the count of the consecutive errors (usually timeouts) against this VC in cross-network heartbeat polling.

wfFrSwVcDropExcessBurstFrames.name: wfFrSwVcDropExcessBurstFrames
wfFrSwVcDropExcessBurstFrames.description: Indicates the number of Excess Burst Frames dropped on this virtual circuit.

wfFrSwVcDropExcessBurstOctets.name: wfFrSwVcDropExcessBurstOctets
wfFrSwVcDropExcessBurstOctets.description: Indicates the number of Excess Burst Octets dropped on this virtual circuit.

wfFrSwVcInBeOctets.name: wfFrSwVcInBeOctets
wfFrSwVcInBeOctets.description: Indicates the maximum number Incoming Excess Burst bytes that are allowed in a configured time interval (T).

wfFrSwVcCfgInBe.name: wfFrSwVcCfgInBe
wfFrSwVcCfgInBe.description: The number of Excess Burst in bits

wfFrSwVcRedirectAction.name: wfFrSwVcRedirectAction
wfFrSwVcRedirectAction.description: Perform pvc source redirect manually or based on cross-net updates: 'redirecttoprimary(2)' will force to switch to primary; 'redirecttobackup(3)' will force to switch to backup; 'switchondemand(4)' will switch based on cross-net status of the primary to and from primary; 'swondemandtoprimary(5)' will switch to primary from backup iff cross-net of primary became active; 'swondemandtobackup(6)' will switch to backup from primary iff cross-net of primary became inactive.

wfFrSwVcRedirectType.name: wfFrSwVcRedirectType
wfFrSwVcRedirectType.description: Type of dte notification at switching time: 'transparent(1)' will not send notification to dte; 'intrusiven(2)' will send async update with NEW bit; 'intrusivea(3)' will send async update with A bit not set.

wfFrSwVcRedirectState.name: wfFrSwVcRedirectState
wfFrSwVcRedirectState.description: PVC Source Redirect State: 'backupinactive(1)' - backup is not configured and/or cross-net status is inactive; will allow traffic only through primary. 'primaryactive(2)' - both primary and backup rx'ed 'active' cross-net status, currently primary is active and traffic only through primary. 'switchtobackup(3)' - primary cross-net status is inactive, but can not switch to backup due to manual (or semi-manual) operation of the redirect; will allow traffic only through primary. 'backupactive(12)' - cross-net status is 'inactive' for primary; will allow traffic only through backup. 'switchtoprimary(13)' - cross-net status is 'active' for primary, should by can not switch to primary due to manual (or semi-manual) operation of the redirect; will allow traffic only through backup. 'holddown(21)' - down state used as intermediate state at switching time (for not more then a second); all traffic is dropped.

wfFrSwVcBackupCalledIpAddr.name: wfFrSwVcBackupCalledIpAddr
wfFrSwVcBackupCalledIpAddr.description: Backup Called Ip Address of the remote end of the PVC.

wfFrSwVcBackupCalledDlci.name: wfFrSwVcBackupCalledDlci
wfFrSwVcBackupCalledDlci.description: Backup Called Dlci of the remote end of the PVC.

wfFrSwVcBackupCrossNetStatus.name: wfFrSwVcBackupCrossNetStatus
wfFrSwVcBackupCrossNetStatus.description: Cross net status of the backup remote end of the PVC.

wfFrSwVcBackupCrossNetErrors.name: wfFrSwVcBackupCrossNetErrors
wfFrSwVcBackupCrossNetErrors.description: Support counter of missed cross net update from backup remote end of the PVC, range: [0, wfFrSwDlcmiCrossNetErrorThreshold].

wfFrSwVcAtmIwfMode.name: wfFrSwVcAtmIwfMode
wfFrSwVcAtmIwfMode.description: This attribute indicates the mode of FR-ATM interworking over this FR PVC or that FR-ATM interworking is not enabled on it.

wfFrSwVcAtmIwfVPI.name: wfFrSwVcAtmIwfVPI
wfFrSwVcAtmIwfVPI.description: This is relevant only when the ATM/FR interworking is enabled for this PVC. This indicates the ATM virtual path identifier associated with the Frame Relay PVC described by this record virtual circuit identifier.

wfFrSwVcAtmIwfVCI.name: wfFrSwVcAtmIwfVCI
wfFrSwVcAtmIwfVCI.description: This is relevant only when FR/ATM interworking is enabled for this PVC. This indicates the ATM virtual circuit identifier associated with the Frame Relay PVC described by this record.

wfFrSwVcAtmIwfLossPriorityPolicy.name: wfFrSwVcAtmIwfLossPriorityPolicy
wfFrSwVcAtmIwfLossPriorityPolicy.description: This is relevant only when FR/ATM interworking is enabled for this FR PVC. This indicates the policy for translating ATM CLP to FR DE on this PVC or simply setting FR DE to a constant value for all frames.

wfFrSwVcAtmIwfDePolicy.name: wfFrSwVcAtmIwfDePolicy
wfFrSwVcAtmIwfDePolicy.description: This is relevant only when FR/ATM interworking is enabled for this FR PVC. This indicates the policy on this PVC for translating FR DE to ATM CLP or simply setting CLP to a constant value for all frames.

wfFrSwVcAtmIwfEfciPolicy.name: wfFrSwVcAtmIwfEfciPolicy
wfFrSwVcAtmIwfEfciPolicy.description: This is relevant only when FR/ATM interworking is enabled for this FR PVC. This indicates the policy on this PVC for translating FR FECN to ATM EFCI or simply setting ATM EFCI to a constant value for all frames.

wfFrSwVcEscapeEnable.name: wfFrSwVcEscapeEnable
wfFrSwVcEscapeEnable.description: Identifies this PVC as either a standard FRSW PVC (escape disabled) or an Escape PVC (escape enabled). The type of Escape PVC (ingress node or egress node) is specified in the wfFrSwDlcmiEntry Object.

wfFrSwVcSpvcCallState.name: wfFrSwVcSpvcCallState
wfFrSwVcSpvcCallState.description: Indicates to the state of the SPVC call for this DLCI.

wfFrSwVcCallReqCalledAddr.name: wfFrSwVcCallReqCalledAddr
wfFrSwVcCallReqCalledAddr.description: Called E.164/X.121 Address for an SPVC Call Request Agent. The address type is determined by the wfFrSwDlcmiL2AddrType attribute in wfFrSwDlcmiEntry.

wfFrSwVcCallReqDlciSelectionType.name: wfFrSwVcCallReqDlciSelectionType
wfFrSwVcCallReqDlciSelectionType.description: Indicates to the Calling End of an SPVC Call Request whether to use any available DLCI, or a specific DLCI. If 'specific' is chosen, the called DLCI value is specified in wfFrSwVcCallReqCalledDlci.

wfFrSwVcCallReqCalledDlci.name: wfFrSwVcCallReqCalledDlci
wfFrSwVcCallReqCalledDlci.description: Indicates to the Calling End of an SPVC Call Request the DLCI to be used at the destination of a virtual circuit. This value should be specified when 'specific' wfFrSwVcCallReqDlciSelectionType is chosen.

wfFrSwVcCallReqRetryTimer.name: wfFrSwVcCallReqRetryTimer
wfFrSwVcCallReqRetryTimer.description: Indicates the number of minutes the Call Request Agent should wait for an SPVC CONNECT message before declaring a Call Setup request REJECTED.

wfFrSwVcCallReqMaxRetries.name: wfFrSwVcCallReqMaxRetries
wfFrSwVcCallReqMaxRetries.description: Indicates the number of times the Call Request Agent should retry failed Call Setup requests before declaring the SPVC invalid.

wfFrSwIsdnBaseTable.name: wfFrSwIsdnBaseTable
wfFrSwIsdnBaseTable.description: This is a FRSW over ISDN configuration table. This table specifies whether the Calling Party (ANI) or Called Party (DNIS) ISDN Phone Number should be used to map the ISDN call to a particular FRSW UNI. The table is indexed by the Slot Number where the PRI(s) exist.

wfFrSwIsdnBaseDelete.name: wfFrSwIsdnBaseDelete
wfFrSwIsdnBaseDelete.description: Indication to delete this FRSW ISDN interface.

wfFrSwIsdnBaseSlotNum.name: wfFrSwIsdnBaseSlotNum
wfFrSwIsdnBaseSlotNum.description: This number is the Slot Number for the PRI interface(s) that are being configured for FRSW ISDN. There will be one of these tables for every slot where an FRSW ISDN PRI Interface exists.

wfFrSwIsdnBaseAssocType.name: wfFrSwIsdnBaseAssocType
wfFrSwIsdnBaseAssocType.description: Indicates which ISDN Phone Number (ANI or DNIS) to use to do the ISDN call to FRSW UNI mapping.

wfFrSwIsdnAssocTable.name: wfFrSwIsdnAssocTable
wfFrSwIsdnAssocTable.description: This table defines the Association Table to be used for the FRSW over ISDN application. The table contains a list of ISDN Phone Numbers and the associated FRSW UNI Index Number. The table is indexed by the Slot Number and the ISDN Phone Number.

wfFrSwIsdnAssocDelete.name: wfFrSwIsdnAssocDelete
wfFrSwIsdnAssocDelete.description: Indication to delete this Association Instance.

wfFrSwIsdnAssocSlotNum.name: wfFrSwIsdnAssocSlotNum
wfFrSwIsdnAssocSlotNum.description: Slot with which this ISDN Phone Number is associated.

wfFrSwIsdnAssocNum.name: wfFrSwIsdnAssocNum
wfFrSwIsdnAssocNum.description: ISDN Phone Number that is used to look up the appropriate FRSW UNI Index. This number is compared with either the Calling Party Number (ANI) Information Element or the Called Party Number (DNIS) Information Element contained in the ISDN Call Setup Message.

wfFrSwIsdnAssocScrnEnable.name: wfFrSwIsdnAssocScrnEnable
wfFrSwIsdnAssocScrnEnable.description: Indicate whether allowed screening should be enabled or disabled for all of the UNIs contained in the FRSW UNI Index.

wfFrSwIsdnAssocIndex.name: wfFrSwIsdnAssocIndex
wfFrSwIsdnAssocIndex.description: A number that indicates the FRSW UNI Index that is is associated with the ISDN Phone Number. This FRSW UNI Index is used as a key to obtain the UNIs and the Screening information from the wfFrSwIsdnScrnEntry and wfFrSwIsdnUniEntry mibs. The default for the index is 2**31 - 1 = 2147483647 = 0x7FFFFFFF, which represents an unconfigured index number.

wfFrSwIsdnUniTable.name: wfFrSwIsdnUniTable
wfFrSwIsdnUniTable.description: This table is used by the FRSW over ISDN application. The table defines a list of FRSW UNIs that are to be collected into a hunt group identifiable by an Index Number.

wfFrSwIsdnUniDelete.name: wfFrSwIsdnUniDelete
wfFrSwIsdnUniDelete.description: Indication to delete this FRSW UNI Index Instance.

wfFrSwIsdnUniIndex.name: wfFrSwIsdnUniIndex
wfFrSwIsdnUniIndex.description: FRSW UNI Index -- a number that identifies a group of related FRSW UNIs that are collected together as a hunt group. This number ties this entry to an entry in wfFrSwIsdnAssocEntry.

wfFrSwIsdnUniState.name: wfFrSwIsdnUniState
wfFrSwIsdnUniState.description: State of this UNI (available or in-use).

wfFrSwIsdnScrnTable.name: wfFrSwIsdnScrnTable
wfFrSwIsdnScrnTable.description: This is the incoming call screening table for the FRSW over ISDN application. The table consists of a FRSW UNI Index and a list of allowable ISDN Phone numbers for that FRSW UNI Index. The table is indexed by both the FRSW UNI Index and the ISDN Phone Number. This table is referenced only when the wfFrSwIsdnAssocScrnEnable is set to Enabled for this FRSW UNI Index.

wfFrSwIsdnScrnDelete.name: wfFrSwIsdnScrnDelete
wfFrSwIsdnScrnDelete.description: Indication to delete this Scrn Instance.

wfFrSwIsdnScrnIndex.name: wfFrSwIsdnScrnIndex
wfFrSwIsdnScrnIndex.description: FRSW UNI Index - A number that ties this entry to an entry in wfFrSwIsdnAssocEntry.

wfFrSwIsdnScrnNum.name: wfFrSwIsdnScrnNum
wfFrSwIsdnScrnNum.description: ISDN Phone Number of a user authorized to access the UNIs contained in the FRSW UNI Index.

wfFrSwSigTable.name: wfFrSwSigTable
wfFrSwSigTable.description: The Frame relay signalling table contains frame relay signalling entries indexed by the frame relay access channel circuit number. An instance of wfFrSwSigEntry is required for each frame relay access channel with frame relay signalling enabled. The absence of wfFrSwSigEntry for a given frame relay access channel implies that frame relay signalling is disabled for the circuit. Note that the terms 'incoming' and 'outgoing' refer to the frame mode call with respect to the network side of the interface. The terminology used by CCITT Q.933/Q.931 is different.

wfFrSwSigEntry.name: wfFrSwSigEntry
wfFrSwSigEntry.description: An entry in the Frame Relay signalling port information table.

wfFrSwSigCircuit.name: wfFrSwSigCircuit
wfFrSwSigCircuit.description: The circuit number for this frame relay access channel

wfFrSwSigSvcDlciLow.name: wfFrSwSigSvcDlciLow
wfFrSwSigSvcDlciLow.description: Lowest DLCI to be used for SVC, the default value is for 2 octet frame header

wfFrSwSigSvcDlciHigh.name: wfFrSwSigSvcDlciHigh
wfFrSwSigSvcDlciHigh.description: Highest DLCI to be used for SVC, the default value is for 2 octet frame header.

wfFrSwSigDlciAssign.name: wfFrSwSigDlciAssign
wfFrSwSigDlciAssign.description: Determines if DLCI's are assigned starting at wfFrSwSigSvcDlciHigh and working towards wfFrSwSigSvcDlciLow or vice versa.

wfFrSwSigMaxNumOfSvcs.name: wfFrSwSigMaxNumOfSvcs
wfFrSwSigMaxNumOfSvcs.description: Indicates the maximum number of simultaneous switched virtual circuits allowed on the logical line.

wfFrSwSigNumOfSvcsInUse.name: wfFrSwSigNumOfSvcsInUse
wfFrSwSigNumOfSvcsInUse.description: Indicates the number of switched virtual circuits in use on the logical line.

wfFrSwSigDefaultThroughput.name: wfFrSwSigDefaultThroughput
wfFrSwSigDefaultThroughput.description: This value is used by the network in the Link Layer Core Parameters IE incoming & outgoing throughput fields when they are not included in the setup message by the user.

wfFrSwSigDefaultMinAcceptThroughput.name: wfFrSwSigDefaultMinAcceptThroughput
wfFrSwSigDefaultMinAcceptThroughput.description: This value is used by the network in the Link Layer Core Parameters IE incoming & outgoing minimum acceptable throughput fields when they are not included in the setup message by the user.

wfFrSwSigDefaultBc.name: wfFrSwSigDefaultBc
wfFrSwSigDefaultBc.description: This value is used by the network in the Link Layer Core Parameters IE incoming & outgoing Bc fields when they are not included in the setup message by the user.

wfFrSwSigDefaultBe.name: wfFrSwSigDefaultBe
wfFrSwSigDefaultBe.description: This value is used by the network in the Link Layer Core Parameters IE incoming & outgoing Be fields when they are not included in the setup message by the user.

wfFrSwSigMaxInThroughputPerSvc.name: wfFrSwSigMaxInThroughputPerSvc
wfFrSwSigMaxInThroughputPerSvc.description: This is the maximum incoming throughput that any single SVC may negotiate for a call. Calls requesting in excess of this attribute are rejected.

wfFrSwSigMaxOutThroughputPerSvc.name: wfFrSwSigMaxOutThroughputPerSvc
wfFrSwSigMaxOutThroughputPerSvc.description: This is the maximum outgoing throughput that any single SVC may negotiate for a call. Calls requesting in excess of this attribute are rejected.

wfFrSwSigTotalInNegotiableThroughput.name: wfFrSwSigTotalInNegotiableThroughput
wfFrSwSigTotalInNegotiableThroughput.description: This is the total maximum incoming throughput that is available for all frame mode calls on the port. If the sum of the incoming throughput requested by a call and wfFrSwSigTotalInCurrentThroughput is in excess of this value, the call is rejected.

wfFrSwSigTotalInCurrentThroughput.name: wfFrSwSigTotalInCurrentThroughput
wfFrSwSigTotalInCurrentThroughput.description: This is the total incoming throughput that has been negotiated for use by all SVC's on the port.

wfFrSwSigTotalOutNegotiableThroughput.name: wfFrSwSigTotalOutNegotiableThroughput
wfFrSwSigTotalOutNegotiableThroughput.description: This is the total maximum outgoing throughput that is available for all frame mode calls on the port. If the sum of the outgoing throughput requested by a call and wfFrSwSigTotalOutCurrentThroughput is in excess of this value, the call is rejected.

wfFrSwSigTotalOutCurrentThroughput.name: wfFrSwSigTotalOutCurrentThroughput
wfFrSwSigTotalOutCurrentThroughput.description: This is the total incoming throughput that has been negotiated for use by all SVC's on the port.

wfFrSwSigXNetClearingDisable.name: wfFrSwSigXNetClearingDisable
wfFrSwSigXNetClearingDisable.description: If cross-net polling (wfFrSwDlcmiCrossNetEnable) is enabled on this interface, and the error threshold (wfFrSwDlcmiCrossNetErrorThreshold) is exceeded, the network can clear the call.

wfFrSwSigCallingPartyIEMandatory.name: wfFrSwSigCallingPartyIEMandatory
wfFrSwSigCallingPartyIEMandatory.description: Reject the call if the Calling Party IE is absent in the setup message or if the provided Calling Party IE fails address authentication tests againt the configured address(es) on the ingress logical line.

wfFrSwSigT301.name: wfFrSwSigT301
wfFrSwSigT301.description: Timer number: T301 default time-out: 3 min state of call: call initiated cause for start: incoming setup normal stop: outgoing connect at the first expiry: clear call at the second expiry: timer not restarted

wfFrSwSigT303.name: wfFrSwSigT303
wfFrSwSigT303.description: Timer number: T303 default time-out: 4 s state of call: call present cause for start: outgoing setup normal stop: incoming connect/call-proceeding/ release-complete at the first expiry: retransmit setup, restart T303 at the second expiry: clear call

wfFrSwSigT305.name: wfFrSwSigT305
wfFrSwSigT305.description: Timer number: T305 default time-out: 30 s state of call: disconnect ind cause for start: outgoing disconnect normal stop: incoming release/disconnect at the first expiry: outgoing release at the second expiry: timer not restarted

wfFrSwSigT308.name: wfFrSwSigT308
wfFrSwSigT308.description: Timer number: T308 default time-out: 4 s state of call: release req cause for start: outgoing release normal stop: incoming release/release-complete at the first expiry: retransmit release, restart T308 at the second expiry: place access channel in maintenance

wfFrSwSigT310.name: wfFrSwSigT310
wfFrSwSigT310.description: Timer number: T310 default time-out: 10 s state of call: incoming call proceeding cause for start: incoming call proceeding normal stop: incoming connect/disconnect at the first expiry: clear call at the second expiry: timer not restarted

wfFrSwSigT322.name: wfFrSwSigT322
wfFrSwSigT322.description: Timer number: T322 default time-out: 4 s state of call: any call state cause for start: outgoing status enquiry normal stop: incoming status/disconnect/ release/release-complete at the first expiry: retransmit status-enq, restart T322 at the second expiry: resend status enq and restart T322

wfFrSwSigInCallProceedingPkts.name: wfFrSwSigInCallProceedingPkts
wfFrSwSigInCallProceedingPkts.description: number of incoming call proceeding packets

wfFrSwSigInReleaseCompletePkts.name: wfFrSwSigInReleaseCompletePkts
wfFrSwSigInReleaseCompletePkts.description: number of incoming release complete packets

wfFrSwSigInStatusEnquiryPkts.name: wfFrSwSigInStatusEnquiryPkts
wfFrSwSigInStatusEnquiryPkts.description: number of incoming status enquiry packets

wfFrSwSigOutCallProceedingPkts.name: wfFrSwSigOutCallProceedingPkts
wfFrSwSigOutCallProceedingPkts.description: number of outgoing call proceeding packets

wfFrSwSigOutStatusEnquiryPkts.name: wfFrSwSigOutStatusEnquiryPkts
wfFrSwSigOutStatusEnquiryPkts.description: number of outgoing status enquiry packets

wfFrSwSigNwrkAbortedConnections.name: wfFrSwSigNwrkAbortedConnections
wfFrSwSigNwrkAbortedConnections.description: number of connections aborted by network

wfFrSwSigDlciIEAllowed.name: wfFrSwSigDlciIEAllowed
wfFrSwSigDlciIEAllowed.description: Reject the call if the Dlci IE is present in the setup message and wfFrSwSigDlciIEAllowed is set to disabled.

wfFrSwSigX213PriorityIEAllowed.name: wfFrSwSigX213PriorityIEAllowed
wfFrSwSigX213PriorityIEAllowed.description: Reject the call if the X213 Priority IE is present in setup message and wfFrSwSigX213PriorityIEAllowed is set to disabled.

wfFrSwSigMaximumBe.name: wfFrSwSigMaximumBe
wfFrSwSigMaximumBe.description: This value is the maximum allowed Be for a SVC connection

wfFrSwGlobalE164AddrTable.name: wfFrSwGlobalE164AddrTable
wfFrSwGlobalE164AddrTable.description: wfFrSwGlobalE164AddrTable is used by Directory Services to translate a range of E.164 addresses into an internal IP network address. E.164 ranges must not ever overlap.

wfFrSwGlobalE164AddrEntry.name: wfFrSwGlobalE164AddrEntry
wfFrSwGlobalE164AddrEntry.description: An entry in the Frame Relay Global E.164 Address Table.

wfFrSwGlobalE164AddrLow.name: wfFrSwGlobalE164AddrLow
wfFrSwGlobalE164AddrLow.description: Instance identifier; the low end of the E.164 address range. This is an 8-byte fixed length octet string format, right justified with padded leading zeros as necessary.

wfFrSwGlobalE164AddrHigh.name: wfFrSwGlobalE164AddrHigh
wfFrSwGlobalE164AddrHigh.description: Instance identifier; the high end of the E.164 address range. This is an 8-byte fixed length octet string format, right justified with padded leading zeros as necessary.

wfFrSwGlobalE164AddrIPAddr.name: wfFrSwGlobalE164AddrIPAddr
wfFrSwGlobalE164AddrIPAddr.description: This is the internal IP network address associated with this range of E.164 addresses.

wfFrSwGlobalX121AddrTable.name: wfFrSwGlobalX121AddrTable
wfFrSwGlobalX121AddrTable.description: wfFrSwGlobalX121AddrTable is used by Directory Services to translate a range of X.121 addresses into an internal IP network address. X.121 ranges must not ever overlap.

wfFrSwGlobalX121AddrEntry.name: wfFrSwGlobalX121AddrEntry
wfFrSwGlobalX121AddrEntry.description: An entry in the Frame Relay Global X.121 Address Table.

wfFrSwGlobalX121AddrLow.name: wfFrSwGlobalX121AddrLow
wfFrSwGlobalX121AddrLow.description: Instance identifier; the low end of the X.121 address range. This is an 8-byte fixed length octet string format, right justified with padded leading zeros as necessary.

wfFrSwGlobalX121AddrHigh.name: wfFrSwGlobalX121AddrHigh
wfFrSwGlobalX121AddrHigh.description: Instance identifier; the high end of the X.121 address range. This is an 8-byte fixed length octet string format, right justified with padded leading zeros as necessary.

wfFrSwGlobalX121AddrIPAddr.name: wfFrSwGlobalX121AddrIPAddr
wfFrSwGlobalX121AddrIPAddr.description: This is the internal IP network address associated with this range of X.121 addresses.

wfFrSwLocalE164AddrTable.name: wfFrSwLocalE164AddrTable
wfFrSwLocalE164AddrTable.description: wfFrSwLocalE164AddrTable contains E.164 addresses on the local BNX and CUG (Closed User Group) related information.

wfFrSwLocalE164AddrEntry.name: wfFrSwLocalE164AddrEntry
wfFrSwLocalE164AddrEntry.description: An entry in the Frame Relay Local E.164 Address Table.

wfFrSwLocalE164AddrCUG.description: CUG (Closed User Group) information. The structure of the CUG information consists zero or more groups (number of groups can be derived from the OCTET STRING data type of this MIB attribute) of COI structure information. Each COI structure consists of a COI group number (4-byte integer) and a COI list. Each COI list consists of a length field (4-byte integer) which specifies the number of bytes of COI bit-encoded information belonging to this group and the COI information structure. COI information structure is a bit mask field where each bit from left to right represents whether this E.164 address belongs to a particular COI number within this COI group number. Please note that COI group numbers can not be repeated and that the COI group numbers must be in increasing order in the CUG configuration MIB wfFrSwLocalE164AddrCUG defaults to zero COI groups which means no CUG related information and hence this local wfFrSwLocalE164Address is allowed to communicate with all users.
